10 (g) If any easement in gross or other right to restrict use of land or any interest
11 in land has been donated to the Maryland Historical Trust or the Maryland Environmental
12 Trust, damages shall be awarded in any condemnation proceedings under this title to the
13 fee owner and leasehold owner, as their interests may appear, and shall be the fair market
14 value of the land or interest in it, computed as though the easement or other right did not
15 exist.
16 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
17 October 1, 2025.

